1
00:00:11,375 --> 00:00:14,708
♪

2
00:00:18,958 --> 00:00:20,375
Hmph.

3
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:21,666
[HAYAMA grunts]

4
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:23,333
[TACHIBANA]
The boys' inter-high prelims

5
00:00:23,416 --> 00:00:24,791
are right around the corner.

6
00:00:24,875 --> 00:00:27,000
Dig in there like this
is the real thing, got it?

7
00:00:27,083 --> 00:00:28,750
[BOTH grunting]

8
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,166
Aah!

9
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:33,375
[gasps]

10
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:38,166
Game. 21-13. 21-15.

11
00:00:38,250 --> 00:00:39,625
Isehara.

12
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:41,666
[HAYAMA] Sweet match, Gaku.
Man, you're on fire!

13
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:44,333
You might make it
to the finals this year.

14
00:00:44,416 --> 00:00:47,458
I'm all for encouraging others,
but what about your chances?

15
00:00:47,541 --> 00:00:48,791
I can't help it.

16
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:50,750
The two of us
have been playing badminton

17
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:52,250
since elementary school.

18
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,541
Of course I'm invested

19
00:00:53,625 --> 00:00:55,333
in how my friend does
at the tournament.

20
00:00:55,416 --> 00:00:56,291
Oh.

21
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:57,583
[HAYAMA]
And sure, I admit,

22
00:00:57,666 --> 00:01:00,791
I wish I could've
beaten you at least once.

23
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:02,375
But between your fake-outs
and line judgment,

24
00:01:02,458 --> 00:01:03,708
you've got a shot to win.

25
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:04,833
[SORA] It's kind of awkward,
don't you think?

26
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:06,041
Huh?

27
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:08,833
Hmm?

28
00:01:08,916 --> 00:01:10,541
[SORA]
Nagisa and Ayano.

29
00:01:11,958 --> 00:01:13,583
[YU]
Oh, them. Right.

30
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:15,666
I can't believe the finals
will have

31
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:17,666
two girls from our school.

32
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:21,041
Aya's still acting
a little weird, though.

33
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,583
[TACHIBANA claps]

34
00:01:22,666 --> 00:01:26,291
Okay. Good job. Let's pack it in
for the day.

35
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:28,416
-[CONNIE] Ikke sa hurtigt.
-[ALL] Huh?

36
00:01:32,291 --> 00:01:34,958
You and I have some
unfinished business.

37
00:01:35,041 --> 00:01:37,166
You ready?

38
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:39,041
[YU]
Isn't that Connie?

39
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:42,000
[SORA] Why'd she travel
all the way from Miyagi?

40
00:01:42,083 --> 00:01:45,083
Huh. Weird. I kinda figured
she'd be at prelims.

41
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:46,833
-Hmm.
-[SHIWAHIME] We were.

42
00:01:46,916 --> 00:01:49,166
But the competition already
wrapped up last weekend.

43
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:52,166
Not bragging or anything,
but Connie and I won.

44
00:01:52,250 --> 00:01:56,791
Wow! Fredericia has a lot
of talent in one school.

45
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:58,166
-[YU] Wait a sec.
-[SORA] Huh?

46
00:01:58,250 --> 00:01:59,958
You're here too, Shiwahime?

47
00:02:00,041 --> 00:02:01,833
I hope we're not intruding.

48
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:03,791
Hmph.

49
00:02:03,875 --> 00:02:07,125
I made a promise to you,
remember?

50
00:02:07,208 --> 00:02:10,250
A one-on-one match
with zero distractions.

51
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:14,166
Huh? Uh, what?

52
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:16,541
-Short skirt.
-So what?

53
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:22,291
[groans, yells]

54
00:02:23,916 --> 00:02:26,375
No one was
making you look, perv!

55
00:02:26,458 --> 00:02:29,208
Why is she embarrassed?
They look cute.

56
00:02:29,291 --> 00:02:30,458
Uh...

57
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,000
It'll be a one-set match.
Get your racquet and let's go.

58
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,416
Connie.
What did we talk about?

59
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,875
[AYANO]
I don't mind playing her.

60
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,541
Are you sure, Ayano?

61
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:18,416
You should be concentrating
on the finals coming up.

62
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:20,916
[gasps]

63
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,500
The most terrible thing
in the world has just happened.

64
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:29,375
My racquet bag's Wei-Wei!
It's dead!

65
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:30,666
[ELENA] You used it
as a zipper pull.

66
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,916
It was bound to happen.

67
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,708
-Who is this Wei-Wei?
-You'll find out.

68
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,250
-[AYANO crying]
-[ELENA] It's a clean break.

69
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,791
Just glue it back together.

70
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:40,583
[AYANO] You don't understand!
He'll never be the same!

71
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,666
[SHIWAHIME]
I have an idea.

72
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:46,291
Why not skip the match,
and instead we can go here?

73
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:50,375
I'd be surprised if we couldn't
find a replacement for you.

74
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,416
-Genius!
-What?

75
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,458
I'm coming, Wei-Wei!

76
00:04:54,541 --> 00:04:55,875
But our match.

77
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:57,375
-[ELENA] Shiwahime.
-Hmm?

78
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:01,000
Having Connie and Ayano
spend the whole day together,

79
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:02,333
could end badly.

80
00:05:02,416 --> 00:05:03,958
[inaudible]

81
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:08,083
What does it matter?

82
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:10,333
I don't need a mom.

83
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:12,541
[AYANO laughs]
Wei-Wei!

84
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:13,916
I'll play chaperone.

85
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,750
You don't have anything
to worry about.

86
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,583
[CONNIE] Are we going
to play or what?

87
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:19,250
[SHIWAHIME]
Connie?

88
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:20,791
Huh?

89
00:05:20,875 --> 00:05:23,250
You're not forgetting
the real reason you came here?

90
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:26,583
But I already
changed my outfit.

91
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,416
Well, we're gonna go ahead

92
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,166
and borrow Ayano
for the afternoon.

93
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,666
I'll tell Wei-Wei you said hi!

94
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,166
[TACHIBANA]
Don't stay out too late.

95
00:05:37,083 --> 00:05:38,958
Uh... Hmm.

96
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:41,000
I bet they're going
to need a manager.

97
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:47,000
[YU] Whew. Feels like we barely
avoided a major storm.

98
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:48,875
[SORA]
Are they gonna be okay?

99
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:52,166
[HAYAMA] Elena's with them.
I'm sure they'll be fine.

100
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,416
Not like we were going
to change Ayano's mind.

101
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,916
I guess you're right.

102
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,875
Anyway, we should
probably head out

103
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:00,458
and get some rest
before the matches start.

104
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:01,833
Hmm.

105
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:06,541
Wanna stop somewhere
on the way home?

106
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,458
[NAGISA]
Riko. help me with drills.

107
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:10,583
[RIKO]
Oh. Uh, sure.

108
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,541
Hey. Go home.

109
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,041
You could use the rest.

110
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:16,000
In a little while.

111
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,291
[sighs]

112
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,500
[AYANO]
We meet at last!

113
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:25,250
-So fluffy!
-Wei!

114
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:29,041
[ELENA] Legs aside, this thing
is a whale shark, right?

115
00:06:29,125 --> 00:06:30,333
How does that work?

116
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:33,041
Sharks are fish
and whales are mammals.

117
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:35,041
[SHIWAHIME] And how'd he get
that hat on his head

118
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:36,333
without arms?

119
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:38,166
A total waste of time
is what I call it.

120
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:39,750
[AYANO] Hey, Wei-Wei.
Give us a pose.

121
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:43,375
Wei, Wei-Wei-Wei!

122
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:45,083
[BOTH]
So adorable!

123
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:47,166
More like creepy.
I was being ironic.

124
00:06:47,250 --> 00:06:49,125
-[AYANO] Take a picture!
-[ELENA] If you'll hold still.

125
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:52,375
Go! Don't fail me!

126
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:54,583
Maybe this time. Looks perfect.

127
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,583
[groans]
I lost!

128
00:06:57,666 --> 00:06:59,125
[ELENA sighs]
You're gonna be here all day.

129
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:01,958
Give someone else a shot.

130
00:07:02,041 --> 00:07:04,625
Oh! But I feel it.
This time I'll win.

131
00:07:04,708 --> 00:07:06,083
[ELENA] Scoot.
You're holding up the line.

132
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:07,791
Now watch how it's done.

133
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,750
[SHIWAHIME] Ooh.
I'm going for the green one.

134
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,791
He looks easy to nab.

135
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,250
-[ELENA] Point it out.
-[SHIWAHIME] There!

136
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:16,250
The one next to.
Yep, that one.

137
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:18,708
[AYANO gasping]
Oh!

138
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:20,791
Come on. So close.

139
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:23,500
[ELENA]
Is that a prize?

140
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:26,708
[CONNIE]
Bingo.

141
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,666
[chuckles]

142
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,541
[MAN]
Congratulations, young lady.

143
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:34,208
[SHIWAHIME and ELENA]
It's huge!

144
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:36,291
You are the proud owner
of an oversized

145
00:07:36,375 --> 00:07:37,625
Wei-Wei backpack.

146
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:39,083
[SHIWAHIME]
No, thank you.

147
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:40,750
Well, you could take it home
as a kind of trophy

148
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,666
and hide it deep
in your closet.

149
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,458
Or maybe exchange it
for something else?

150
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,791
[AYANO]
So lucky!

151
00:07:46,875 --> 00:07:49,250
Do you wanna adopt him, Ayano?

152
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:52,416
You mean it? Yay!

153
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:53,625
[CONNIE]
What's going on?

154
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:55,958
Look, Connie!

155
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:57,708
-Where have you been?
-Check it out!

156
00:07:57,791 --> 00:08:00,375
[ELENA] Shiwahime won it
on her first try.

157
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:01,458
Crazy, huh?

158
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:02,625
[SHIWAHIME]
It was pure luck.

159
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,416
[AYANO laughs]
And he's all mine!

160
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,125
[ELENA]
What's the polite thing to say?

161
00:08:06,208 --> 00:08:07,416
[AYANO]
Thank you.

162
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,833
[SHIWAHIME chuckles]

163
00:08:08,916 --> 00:08:11,666
It'd be hard for me
to take it home, anyway.

164
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:14,625
Oh, hey. Have you guys
ever cosplayed before?

165
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:19,958
Elena. I need saving.

166
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,083
Ugh. How old are you?

167
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,541
Come on over here.

168
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,750
-[ALL gasp]
-Huh?

169
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,416
[CONNIE] You should be able
to do that by yourself.

170
00:08:37,583 --> 00:08:42,083
But at least it's cute, I guess.

171
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:44,666
[chuckles]

172
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:45,958
[ALL]
One, two.

173
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,750
[camera shutter clicking]

174
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:53,500
[MIYU’S SISTER]
Can I have half?

175
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:55,500
[ELENA]
Whale-shaped meat buns?

176
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,916
[SHIWAHIME] Sounds intriguing,
but I'll pass.

177
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,166
[AYANO grunting]
Wei-Wei!

178
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,750
Everywhere you turn,
you can't escape Wei-Wei.

179
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:08,208
[AYANO] You have no idea
what you're missing.

180
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:10,000
Hmm?

181
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:11,500
Take a bite. It's magic.

182
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:15,208
[chuckles]

183
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:18,833
You know what?

184
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:20,916
I think I'm gonna go
buy us some drinks.

185
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,333
Elena, wanna come
with me and help?

186
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:24,583
Huh?

187
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,375
Uh... Sure.
See you guys in a bit.

188
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:31,833
Later.

189
00:09:42,875 --> 00:09:44,666
Thanks a bunch
for doing this.

190
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,541
Of course.

191
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:48,541
Ayano's genuinely happy.

192
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:50,750
It's been a while
since that's happened.

193
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,333
I'm glad.

194
00:09:54,416 --> 00:09:56,583
And let's hope the mood carries
for the rest of the day.

195
00:10:00,041 --> 00:10:01,875
-[CONNIE] Ugh!
-[AYANO] What'd she say?

196
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:03,083
[CONNIE]
Uh...

197
00:10:03,166 --> 00:10:05,125
They saw a hot guy and,
you know,

198
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:06,666
checking him out and stuff.

199
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:08,541
Getting an eyeful before
they start heading back our way.

200
00:10:08,625 --> 00:10:10,750
Sounds boring.

201
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,750
Hmm.

202
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:13,916
[AYANO]
♪ I say hey ♪

203
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,166
-♪ You say Wei-Wei ♪
-Um...

204
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,625
-Hey, Ayano.
-♪ Wei-Wei ♪

205
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:18,208
Hmm? What is it?

206
00:10:19,416 --> 00:10:23,125
I was wondering,
if you would want...

207
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:24,208
If I'd want to?

208
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:26,000
Nothing. Forget it.

209
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:28,125
What? You can't do that.

210
00:10:28,208 --> 00:10:30,791
-It wasn't important, okay?
-No fair.

211
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,666
That makes me want to know
what it is even more.

212
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:34,875
Wei!

213
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:36,500
[grunts]

214
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:38,375
What did I just get
through telling you?

215
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:39,541
[MIYU’S SISTER]
Forget it.

216
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:42,291
Miyu.

217
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,500
You took that from your sister
without asking.

218
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:48,291
Now, do you have
something to say?

219
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:52,041
♪

220
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:57,958
[sighs]

221
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:09,291
I'm... sorry.

222
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:11,791
I shouldn't have.

223
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,958
-It's okay.
-[MOM chuckles]

224
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:17,250
-[MIYU] You mean it?
-Yeah.

225
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,875
Aww. My little angels!

226
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:20,541
Tell you what,
let's eat the rest

227
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,375
of these
Wei-Wei buns at home.

228
00:11:22,458 --> 00:11:23,708
[GIRLS]
Okay.

229
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:27,375
[MIYU] I was wondering,
where does Wei-Wei live?

230
00:11:27,458 --> 00:11:30,041
[MIYU’S SISTER]
Planet Wei-Wei, duh.

231
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:32,500
[ELENA] We're back, Ayano.
Sorry for the wait.

232
00:11:33,541 --> 00:11:36,041
[AYANO] There you are.
What took you so long?

233
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:39,250
[CONNIE]
I want us to be a family.

234
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,708
That's why I came along.

235
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:46,083
I wanted to tell you everything.
How I felt.

236
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,875
I can't help myself.

237
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,625
What I want most...

238
00:11:57,458 --> 00:12:00,708
is for the three of us
to become a family.

239
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:04,250
You, me and Mama.
Living together.

240
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,708
I know just where
we should go

241
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:18,291
to give our day
the perfect finish.

242
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:20,125
[SORA and YU laughing]

243
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,750
Speaking of, I think I remember
hearing you

244
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,833
and your brother have been
friends with Hayama forever,

245
00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:27,666
like before you guys
were even ten?

246
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:28,666
Yep.

247
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,166
Ever since elementary school.

248
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,625
[YU]
And it was Gaku, wasn't it?

249
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:35,208
Who started both you guys
playing badminton?

250
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:36,666
-So...
-Nope.

251
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,833
The other way around.
Hayama was already playing

252
00:12:38,916 --> 00:12:41,583
and he suggested my brother
and me give the sport a go.

253
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:44,708
[inaudible]

254
00:12:47,125 --> 00:12:48,458
I didn't know.

255
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:51,750
Oh. It's about time to leave.

256
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,125
Sorry. I have to run an errand.

257
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:56,666
Oh. Bye.

258
00:13:08,708 --> 00:13:10,291
You said you wanted to play.

259
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,333
Yeah.

260
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:19,208
Ready when you are.

261
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:38,250
[CONNIE]
What?

262
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:43,000
The shuttlecock, if you will.

263
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:45,666
-Are you for real?
-What's the hold up?

264
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,291
You wanted to play me,
and that's what we're doing.

265
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,458
[gasps]

266
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:55,583
-Connie.
-No.

267
00:13:55,666 --> 00:13:57,208
She's right.

268
00:13:57,291 --> 00:13:59,666
We communicate
through badminton.

269
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:02,625
We're Uchika's children.
It's our shared language.

270
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,125
[AYANO] Let's get this
over with already.

271
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:14,666
Gor det alvorligt, Ayano.

272
00:14:21,791 --> 00:14:23,500
[grunting]

273
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,791
[panting]

274
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:49,750
[sighs]

275
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:54,708
It's me.

276
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,333
Hey, wait up!

277
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:57,583
I brought you a...

278
00:15:02,958 --> 00:15:04,500
Hmph!

279
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:06,083
Good luck, you dum-dum.

280
00:15:07,541 --> 00:15:08,916
[RIKO]
Last one.

281
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:16,791
Seems like a good place to stop.

282
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:17,875
I can keep going.

283
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,083
[RIKO]
But you're...

284
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:20,708
[NAGISA]
If I'm not moving, I get edgy.

285
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:27,750
I can't let myself forget.

286
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:29,666
I'm going to be fighting her.

287
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:32,000
The same Ayano from last year.

288
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:39,708
[gasps]

289
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,666
It's like night and day.

290
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,750
Ayano has completely
changed up her playing style.

291
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:46,875
[panting]

292
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:49,791
[AYANO]
That makes it 13-5.

293
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:52,500
[CONNIE]
Ayano, be my family.

294
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:58,125
Acknowledge me.

295
00:15:58,208 --> 00:15:59,708
Please, sister!

296
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:03,625
♪

297
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:11,875
[inaudible]

298
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:20,875
Rumor is, you're the most
talented student here.

299
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:23,000
Wanna play?

300
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:24,333
[chuckles]

301
00:16:26,708 --> 00:16:28,583
[indistinct chatter]

302
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:31,708
Not bad. How about this?

303
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:47,166
Hey. How about I be your Mama
and you come and live with me?

304
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:48,583
[gasps]

305
00:16:57,541 --> 00:16:58,750
Huh?

306
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:00,208
Who is this, Mama?

307
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,125
Hmm? Oh.

308
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:03,750
Her name's Ayano.

309
00:17:05,166 --> 00:17:06,958
Ayano?

310
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:08,958
Does she also play badminton?

311
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:09,958
Mm-hmm.

312
00:17:10,041 --> 00:17:11,041
Is she good?

313
00:17:11,125 --> 00:17:13,083
Ah, not bad, I suppose.

314
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:15,416
Better than I am?

315
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,291
That's difficult to judge.

316
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:19,958
Oh.

317
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:23,166
She happens
to be my daughter.

318
00:17:24,416 --> 00:17:28,250
Which would mean,
Ayano is your big sister.

319
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:32,208
Big sister?

320
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,916
[UCHIKA]
She's part of our family.

321
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,166
[humming]

322
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:08,125
[groans]

323
00:18:08,208 --> 00:18:09,958
[panting]

324
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:13,375
Are you ready to
quit for the day?

325
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,375
[CONNIE]
I'm tired,

326
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:21,458
but I bet Ayano
could handle more than this.

327
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:24,041
She's Mama's daughter after all.

328
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:25,500
Not yet.

329
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:32,416
Acknowledge me, Mama.

330
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,500
Acknowledge me, Ayano!

331
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,666
Mama, I have to go.

332
00:18:56,916 --> 00:18:59,000
Hold up a minute.
Are you...

333
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:07,791
Yeah. I ran into her. My sister.

334
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:11,041
I'm not really sure yet, Mama.

335
00:19:11,125 --> 00:19:12,458
I miss you.

336
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:24,125
[heavy breathing]

337
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:37,583
Huh?

338
00:19:37,666 --> 00:19:40,250
[AYANO] Remind me,
what was the score again?

339
00:19:41,458 --> 00:19:43,208
You're not quitting already?

340
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,250
Why?

341
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:51,333
It's impossible.

342
00:19:52,583 --> 00:19:55,000
The three of us
can never be a family.

343
00:19:56,625 --> 00:20:00,250
Because this time, I'm the one
who's abandoning Mom.

344
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:07,916
[NAGISA]
Sorry for the wait, Riko.

345
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,750
Let's go. One more round.

346
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:10,958
-[groans]
-Nagisa.

347
00:20:11,041 --> 00:20:12,291
I'm fine.

348
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:13,875
Don't go easy on me
just 'cause I'm tired.

349
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:17,958
No. If you keep this up,
you're going to injure yourself.

350
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,791
Just one more time.

351
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,458
I need this, Riko.

352
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:33,333
♪

353
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:46,375
Ah. We can still
catch the last bus.

354
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:53,458
[SHIWAHIME] Hey. How much longer
are you going to sulk?

355
00:20:53,541 --> 00:20:55,625
You hung out,
she blew you off.

356
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:58,416
You're upset.
I understand.

357
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:00,125
But you shouldn't
let it get to you.

358
00:21:01,166 --> 00:21:05,000
Just leave me alone.
I didn't ask you to come anyway.

359
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:06,291
[sighs]

360
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:10,000
It's this side of your
personality that annoys me.

361
00:21:11,291 --> 00:21:14,166
What do you guys think?
It's frustrating, right?

362
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:15,958
[TAGAJO]
One hundred percent annoying.

363
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:17,541
[gasps]

364
00:21:17,625 --> 00:21:20,125
[OGATSU] Our youngest is always
getting into trouble.

365
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,750
[USHI] Yeah, but that's what
we love so much about her.

366
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,333
[MISATO]
Psst. Down here.

367
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:27,416
[ALL] Welcome back.
We missed you, Connie.

368
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,166
[gasps]

369
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:30,625
[chuckles]

370
00:21:30,708 --> 00:21:32,291
We thought
you needed a reminder.

371
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:33,916
You've got a family here, too.

372
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,250
[KIDS laughing]

373
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,250
[overlapping chatter]

374
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:44,750
[SHIWAHIME]
Here.

375
00:21:47,375 --> 00:21:49,125
Someday you can
give it to her.

376
00:21:49,208 --> 00:21:52,291
It's late. I guess
we should be heading back.

377
00:21:52,375 --> 00:21:53,958
We're already breaking curfew.

378
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:58,083
[sobbing]

379
00:22:11,208 --> 00:22:12,541
[CONNIE]
Dear Mama,

380
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:15,041
when I see you again,
I want to introduce you

381
00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:17,500
to some important
friends of mine.

382
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:20,666
And one day, I hope my sister
can meet them, too.

383
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,875
[AYANO]
Finally home.

384
00:22:26,958 --> 00:22:28,458
[sighs]

385
00:22:29,916 --> 00:22:31,750
[WOMAN]
Welcome back, Ayano.

386
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:33,041
[gasps]

